title.narrative: Middle East Response – Ensuring continuity of treatment and essential services for people affected by HIV, TB and malaria in Yemen, Syria, Iraq, Jordan, Lebanon and Palestine.

description.narrative: Multicountry Middle East MER - Multicomponent - International Organization for Migration - IOM. This program has the following goals: The goal of the third phase of the MER is to provide essential HIV, TB, and malaria services to eligible country populations in Syria, Yemen, Iraq, Jordan, Lebanon and Palestine.. To build on the achievments of MER 2nd phase scaling up identified interventions for HIV, TB and malaria for impact.. To prevent collapse of service delivery for the three diseases in countries affected by conflict and humanitarian crises and continue to strenghten local health systems. The objectives of this program are: TB: To detect and notify cases of new and relapse TB episode during the years 2022 to 2024 as targeted in each of six countries. TB: To notify and enroll in treatment with 2nd line TB medicines for RR-TB and/or MDR-TB cases in each of six countries during years 2022 to 2024. TB: To progressively reach an annnual tretament success rate for all forms of TB - bacteriologically confirmed plus clinically diagnosed, new and relapse cases during years of 2022 to 2024. HIV : To promote preventive activities in five target countries.. HIV: To enhance HIV testing coverage among key and vulnerable populations. HIV: To enhance ART coverage for all PLHIV. Malaria: To achieve and maintain universal coverage with LLINs priritizing population at risk of malaria through mass campaigns in the targeted districts in Yemen. Malaria :To strengthen malaria prompt diagnosis and effective treatment at public and community sectors according to the national guidelines at all level in Yemen.
